		</font>
		<hr size="1">I highly recomend both a bow and an item, with HP, AC, whatever is best that you can find. Simply switch the item out with the bow when you want to use it and then put it back after, letting you effectively have the best of both worlds. This may seem inconvenient, however it isn't as awkward as you might think, once you get used to it, either get a UI like mine which has the inventory bags listed beside the hotkeys and with inventory slots for ranged, primary, etc in your bags, which makes switching gear easy, http://www.eqinterface.com/ has a godly selection of these. or put your bag (with the bow in it) and the ranged slot in your hotkeys. This way you can have a 10AC plus Hp (i forget the exact stats of what I have, heh) item in your ranged slot but be able to shoot your bow, should you wish.</P><P>Why use a bow instead of stunning? Zero mana cost (not like cease uses that much, eh), The fun of it <img src='http://www.everlore.com/gimages/smile.gif' width=15 height=15 align=middle> ,arrows generate less agro radius and are less likely to attract nearby adds, especially when the critter you are pulling is right beside a lulled mob. (although this appears to be more important during lower levels, at high levels the stun agro generated seems moot, or perhaps they changed this a while back and I never noticed /shrug) Oh yes and also, with a bow you get plenty of opotunity to complain about your skill capping at a meer 75, try and hit the broad side of a barn with that<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
