		<hr size="1">4 heals?  If it works for you, so be it.  However, I find that a waste of space.</P><P>Also, I've never noticed this "spell aggro"...not even in my lower levels.  Granted, I didn't have a nice spell like Cease - which should be memmed pretty much at all times.</P><P>It's much more important, unless you aren't tanking, to have aggro spells over extra heal spells that aren't needed - IMO, of course.</P><P>Typical line-up, in random order:</P><P>Stun - fast cast (Akilae or Akera)<BR>Stun - movement (Quellios - unless fighting mobs too high for it, then Akilae or Akera not memmed already)<BR>Stun - no duration (Cease)<BR>Heal - fast cast<BR>Heal - group, can be changed to HoT if not in a group that will require group heals<BR>Pacify/Root<BR>Haste/Innate (Divine Might/IoN or upgrades)<BR>Most people include Divine Aura - I never use it.  That's just me.  I'd rather have Yaulp here or...if you prefer...your 3rd heal (Sup heal most likely)</P><P>That's in mid 50s or higher.</P><P>At lower levels<BR>Heal - only need one, the others are wastes of mana.<BR>Stun - Largest<BR>Stun - no duration (Cease)<BR>Root<BR>Pacify<BR>Flash of Light<BR>Yaulp<BR>Utility slot that can be used for anything you wish</P><P>Like I said, I've never known a spell to generate more aggro.  Spells don't create aggro fields...this is the first time, I've ever heard it mentioned.  I realize this comes off as calling you a liar, and I don't mean it to sound that way...I just don't know any other way to say it.  You obviously have seen something I've never seen...that's the only thing I can come up with.</P><P>If you don't want stun aggro, then replace Cease (I don't advise it) with Cancel Magic (or similar).</P><P>Pulling aggro is an excellent thing to have, regardless of whether or not you are the tank.  A good warrior can get that aggro off you in one round or even before it even gets to you.  One bow shot can do it, but if it doesn't a single taunt can do it (unless they fail their taunt roll) or combined with a disarm and a kick.</P><P>When they do this, the slower can slow almost immediately w/o them getting aggro from the tank.  But even if they do, you have a fast cast stun to get it back (or better yet, your taunt key since as a puller you didn't use it yet).</P><P>I do agree at the lower levels, especially w/o some form of mana presv, using Cease (at 15 mana) can be mana consuming.  But hell, might as well get that archery skill up to 75 in the lower levels.  But you really shouldn't be using Nightmarewood Compound bows (or even a bow with uber stats) in your lower levels.  If you have the money for something like that, then you have the money to twink the WIS on your char up high enough that 15 mana <I>isn't</i> a big deal.</P><P>/shrug</P><P>To each their own, I guess.<br>&nbsp;<br>&nbsp;<br></font>
	</font>
